<Article
  title="Grade-Adjusted Pace, explained — and why your watch's number might be wrong"
  description="GAP turns a hilly run into the equivalent flat-ground pace. The math comes from Alberto Minetti's 2002 paper. The formula, the implementation, and why two apps disagree on the same run."
